                        Clubb
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1173</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1173</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-05-08T21:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-05-08T21:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-08T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-08T21:00:00-05:00" n="1173" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1173">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.101/5–949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-09T10:00:00+08:00">May 9, 1949—10 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 9—5:34 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>796. ReContel 734 [<hi rend="italic">735</hi>] April 30. Peiping mayor (Contel
                    763, May 4) returned yesterday without comment but letter sent headquarters
                    still unreturned.</p>
                <p>ReContel 732, April 29 [<hi rend="italic">30</hi>],<note n="51" xml:id="d1173fn51">
                        <ref target="frus1949v09#pg_974">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ix</hi>, p.
                            974</ref>.</note> particularly last paragraph. Urge action on matter
                    Japan trade before May 15, if possible, because of possible value for Mukden
                    matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
